<section id="To_create_System_Image_Types2" remap="TID_15509">
	<title>Creating System Image Types for PXE</title>
	<para>
		The following procedure creates a system image type for PXE servers.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Create System Image Types</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>PXE</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guilabel>System Image Types</guilabel> accordion.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/2318.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guibutton>Configuration</guibutton>, then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1848.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guibutton>(Add a new System Image Type)</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In <guilabel>Basic Information</guilabel>, type in a <guilabel>Name</guilabel> and select a <guilabel>Type</guilabel>.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/2317.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Use <guimenuitem>Host</guimenuitem> if you want this image type to only apply to hosts.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Use <guimenuitem>Vm</guimenuitem> if you want this image type to only apply to virtual machines.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Use <guilabel>Any</guilabel> if this image type can be used for either hosts or virtual machines.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
	<note>
		<para>
			After creating the System Image Types, assign the types to each image on your PXE servers. To do this, you will select each image on the PXE server and identify its type.
		</para>
	</note>
</section>